[2] Saudi Arabia: 2 new cases, 1 death, MOH
Date: Fri 21 Jun 2013
Source: Saudi Arabia Ministry of Health [edited]
http://www.moh.gov.sa/en/HealthAwareness/Corona/PressReleases/Pages/MediaStatement-2013-06-21-001.aspx


2 New Cases of Novel Coronavirus Recorded and 1 Case Passed Away
----------------------------------------------------------------
Within the framework of the epidemiological surveillance of the novel coronavirus (MERS-CoV), the Ministry of Health (MOH) has announced that 2 confirmed cases of this virus have been recorded. The 1st case is a 41-year-old Saudi female in Riyadh [Ar Riyad Region], from the contacted people to one of the confirmed cases, but her condition is stable. The 2nd case is a 32-year-old Saudi citizen in the Eastern [Ash Sharqiyah] Region, who is suffering from cancer and now at the ICU receiving the proper treatment.

Within the same vein, MOH has announced the death of one case in the Eastern [Ash Sharqiyah] Region, who had been previously announced to be infected with this virus and admitted to hospital on [26 Apr 2013] (corresponding to 16th of Jumada Al-Akhera, 1434 H).

--
Communicated by:
ProMED-mail
<promed@promedmail.org>

[According to the MOH press release in Arabic, the death occurred in an 81-year-old male in the Eastern [Ash Sharqiyah] Region (see http://www.moh.gov.sa/HealthAwareness/Corona/PressReleases/Pages/mediastatement-2013-06-21-001.aspx).

With the addition of these 2 cases and one death, presumably not included in the WHO update in section [1] of this post, this will bring the global total of laboratory-confirmed cases to 70, including 39 deaths.

This brings the total number of confirmed cases in Saudi Arabia to 55, including 33 deaths.

For the map of Saudi Arabia showing the locations of laboratory-confirmed cases, see http://www.moh.gov.sa/en/HealthAwareness/Corona/Pages/AboutCorona.aspx. - Mod.MPP]

